reviews.text:
A really lay back spot, very modern / casual spot to grab quick food, beer, play a little ping pong
Overall a great experience
Pizza was top tier.  Very creative and tasty.
Short dark skin lady was very friendly and descriptive w/ the menu
56$ for (2) pizzas (2) beers (2) sodas

So I did come here because of the infamy this place got from the Pizza Gate conspiracy and to prove a point that it's actually a pretty nice place and it got all this negative attention because Q followers decided to make this place the center of a made up controversy.

Go outside, touch grass, use your eyes, and most importantly, eat pizza.

Also the garlic knots are good.

Good beer, staff is really nice. Didn't get to play ping pong because they had live music that night but it was a good show. Ordered a margherita pizza as a "build your own" because it's not a menu item and unfortunately they use cherry tomatoes instead of sliced. Other than that everything was great.

Great food with vegan options. My family has gone here for years and they have always provided great service. Their dairy free cheese is honestly amazing. There are 3 ping pong tables in the back, so if you go during peak hours they will likely be occupied.

Great little place to visit for lunch or dinner. Amazing fires on pizzas with a ton of other options on the menu like sandwiches and salads. Several beers on tap, local and otherwise, as well as cans and bottles. Cocktails are available and the bartenders are knowledgeable. There are a handful of ping pong tables in the back that you can play with a bar and seating area for convenience. Prices are good, wait staff and tenders are great, and outdoor seating available.

We came here for dinner and we absolutely loved our experience! The interior of the whole restaurant feels so homey and cozy with the lovely decor and ambiance. The food is delicious, and the service is unbeatable. We ordered from the family style menu, and we got the Caesar salad, Maggiano’s salad, calamari fritté, stuffed mushrooms, famous rigatoni “D”, mom’s lasagna, shrimp scampi, red snapper, and the dessert sampler. Absolutely everything we ordered was phenomenal, and we loved the option of ordering from the family style menu. The service was excellent, and our server was very attentive to our needs at every point throughout the meal. We will definitely be back again for the family style menu when we’re in the area!

The food was delicious, we had breaded chicken and lasagna.  My kids really love those kids' meals with homemade ice cream at the end.  Sydney was really patient and great! We really enjoyed our family time.  Loved the $5 take-home meal deal. Nice holiday music.

Delicious food, and the staff are smart!
Staff here can remember large orders with many alterations, and the food still comes out fast. I wish they had more non-alcoholic drink options, though.

Also, the vibes in here are great! Lovely decor, low lighting is good for a date.
Try the 5$ take-home dinners!

You can get your parking ticket validated here, there is a direct elevator entrance from the parking garage. Highly recommended!

My friend had recommended Maggianos as an anniversary dinner spot so we decided to visit late December. Overall, in terms of food, it’s a bit lackluster. My partner and I suspect the food was microwaved because the pasta did not taste fresh and the mashed potatoes were disappointingly clumped as one doughy ball. We had the eggplant and calamari appetizers, the lasagna, eggplant parmigiana, side of mashed potatoes, tiramisu, and lemon cookies (see photos). Out of all of those, I loved the eggplant appetizer. It’s a heart attack but worth it. My partner loved the calamari appetizer and its dipping tomato sauce.

Also, although our waitress forgot my salmon add-on request to the eggplant pasta and still charged me for it, she was sincerely apologetic when we pointed out the missing salmon and had the receipt edited to have that removed. I gave this 3 stars because despite the food quality of the entrees and sides, this restaurant does have huge portions for their prices and friendly staff and service.

Side note: I would recommend this restaurant for large family or friend get-togethers since when we went, there were kids running around and a group of ladies constantly screaming and squealing as they had some sort of gift opening exchange going on and were throwing their gift wrapping trash everywhere. We had a loud experience so if you’re going for a quiet dinner, avoid the main dining area.

I ordered the lobster carbonara… it’s something I’ve ordered it a few times at the location in a different city. This first time ordering here. The pasta sauce has a very chalky, bitter taste, the lobster was chewy and flavorless and there was not the same amount of bacon. It just didn’t taste as good  unfortunately.

It’s all about the experience when you come here (and the free unlimited bread which is always the best thing on the table) I got the soft chicken tacos and they were 90% onions but the fries were surprisingly good. Our waitress was so so lovely and attentive. She was willing to accommodate our large party and all of our needs. The Long Island iced tea was a nice pour and decent size even though it was a bit pricy. Overall, the vibe is the goal here and it was accomplished based on the bread and the waitress alone.

Great service, hot and prompt food. I tried the clam chowder and salad. It was my first time trying clam chowder and it was pretty good. I also asked to swap the regular salad with the mix greens (no croutons). Everything tasted fresh. Also had a margarita and the sugar free cheesecake. Really surprised at how good that sugar free cheesecake was! Also, our waitress Brittany was excellent and attentive.

Had a great dinner with my boyfriend and mother. Our server was more than great. She went above and beyond for us. Food was pretty good. Wish it was a little better but I know the place is mainly well known for their impeccable cheesecakes! Got the dulce de leche caramel cheesecake and it is delicious!

This will be my first and last time coming to this place . I brought my son here for his 13th  birthday excited hoping for amazing food and good services. Sadly the waitress Sahara was rude and uncaring. She seemed disoriented and confused. She was muttering things  I had to ask her to repeat herself several times not sure if she was new or what her deal was. She asked what we wanted to drink 3 different times as if she not write it down or wasn’t  paying attention. On top of that the food was nasty. Salty wings, soggy asparagus.
I didn’t even get what I asked for I asked for ranch got blue cheese asked for no scallions on the nachos got extra scallions. It was ridiculous. I had mentioned from the beginning it was my sons 13 birthday and that I wanted a surprise birthday song and a slice of velvet cake for him. When she brought us the the slice of cake at the end she didn’t even acknowledge my son and just placed the cake in the table no birthday son no happy birthday just placed it on the table and left. I honestly didn’t want to tip her but not coming to this place ever again solves the problem.

Thank you Ms. Ny for a great late night dining experience!!! You are very professional and an awesome asset to this franchise!!! Note, the pepperoni on the flatbread pizza is somewhat spicy but good. The buffalo blasts are really small in size. In the past, the portion size was more than ample to share this dish. They are not worth $16.00 unless you simply like or love them.  They were very good and the minced-like chicken was tender.

NOTE, the 2 star rating is due to the very RUDE brown-skin lady who works in the bakery.  I politely said excuse me twice while she looked me and my child in the face, ignored us, and continued to wipe down the refrigerated equipment.  Her co-worker was kind enough to acknowledge us.  I explained to her that I don't take food in restrooms and asked her if we could leave our food on the counter until we returned from the restrooms. When we returned to retrieve our food she said have a good evening!!!
The type of disrespect and unprofessionalism she exhibited  is totally unacceptable! What was the purpose? #POORHospitality at the Cheesecake Factory.
Good food and service in a bright and cheerful setting.  The chips had both hot and cold dips and the Steak Quesadillas ($15.95) were delicious.   Conveniently located by the Tenleytown Metro.
We had a great time at Guapo's.  We our office Christmas party here and it was awesome.  The food was delicious and if you like traditional Mexican food then you will live this place.

Great Mexican food!  They have a large menu with many good options. Classics like tacos, enchiladas and fajitas are sure to please. I found that they are very fast bringing the food out too which is really nice.  Plenty of indoor and some outdoor seating as well. Excellent service rounds it all out!
Guapos is awesome. They are always consistent with the quality of their good. This location is one of my favorites.

Great service. This location has outdoor tables w/large umbrellas for shading. Servers all wearing masks. Masks required inside, except when eating, of course.

On-street metered parking using coins or Park Mobile app. Covered parking lot nearby for local shops. Guapo's may validate.

Food was decent. We ordered El Paso tacos (2 chicken & 1 beef), chicken & spinach quesadilla 😋, a side of rice & black beans, and a coke. Food lukewarm. Sides were cold. Refried beans looked and tasted like pureed. Overall, good experience.

My official Memorial Day festivities began with dinner at this surf themed restaurant. It is our second visit and the food and service could not have been better. This kitchen does not mess around. Chef and crew “Bravo!” Our server, Tucker, was phenomenal. He was so professional and polite and flawless. If I was in this industry, I would snatch him in a heartbeat. The frozen spicy margarita was delicious. Hats off to the bartender. The pork al pastor Island Nachos, our appetizer, was delicious. For our entrees, we had the Cayman Islands Enchiladas and the Rock House Bowl. Both were masterfully executed and served piping hot. What a perfect evening! Happy Memorial Day.

Great pork belly sliders and Fries. The Tahiti salad was good but there were WAY too many bean sprouts on it. Every bite tasted like just bean sprouts which is a shame because the dressing, and mango give the salad really good flavor. I started to scoop mine off to the side of my plate. My tip is to ask for no bean sprouts on this salad to truly enjoy it fully.

Always a fan of Surfside ! I usually go to the N street location but today I wanted to try this location and everything was amazing I wasn’t disappointed. Service was amazing. The pork belly sliders is a must. I do recommend giving this location a try if you haven’t or giving Surfside in general a try 👍🏼
Good experience overall. Laid back restaurant. Nice size so you can fit a large party. The Nevis is very delicious and the shrimp is a healthy size. Their rum punch is delightful.

The food and drinks are amazing here! They have many different options that offer a taste of the Caribbean in a taco, burrito or bowl. Some of the staff were nice, but others seemed to second guess themselves when serving us. Almost like the were scared of black people. Other than the random awkwardness, we had a good time. Everything we tried we enjoyed and we appreciated the suggestions from our waiter. I’d definitely give this place another try as I’ve been to the DuPont location and had a totally different experience; I’d definitely love to see an improvement with the interaction I had with some of their staff.

My experience at this nice restaurant was nothing short of perfect. The lychee fruit drink was outstanding. The Curry Laksa was so good, it made me want to buy a ticket to Kuala Lumpur. I definitely cannot forget about the Vietnamese Spring Rolls. They were delicious. The waitress was extremely cool and polite. She talked to us about Malaysia. I definitely will be returning here more frequently.
I moved here 3 months ago and this is the best Asian restaurant I've had in the DMV area so far. The roasted duck noodles are amazing and it feels like my hometown. The lamb satay is very addictive.

Very nice place. Our waitress was so kind and helpful. We had the veggie dumplings and roti canoi. The dumplings had a lot of filling and the roti canoi was incredible and my favorite overall. The pad see ew was pretty good and they had good vegetarian options to switch the orange chicken to a fake chicken.

Great Malaysian food in Washington DC, friendly staff members, reasonably priced. I had a to go order consisting of Beef Rendang and Char Kway Teoy. Both were delicious and authentic enough. The serving portion was also generous for the price. The rendang was tender and kway teoy also tastes great. Definitely would recommend this place!

An excellent family run Asian restaurant with wide array of Asian food selection. Reasonably priced and good quality food.

I was impressed by how quickly the food was prepared and served.

I had first visited Le Chat Noir about 15 years ago, not long after they opened, and somehow had not made it back until Restaurant Week this year. And I'm glad I came back.

The physical space is pretty small and bareboned. The closeness of the tables reminded me of bistros in Europe. It's not as cozy as it could be, though, which is why I have the ambiance just 4 stars.

There seemed to be only three people working the tables, but they were excellent! Moving so quickly and ensuring everyone had everything they needed. The waiter who served us was French-speaking and happy to hear even a few words of French spoken back at him. He was lovely.

The cocktail and wine menu isn't super long, but all that's offered is superb. I enjoyed my Kir Royal and a glass of French Grenache.

And the food - that's the main reason to come! My husband and I got different things, so we could try two of everything, and were quite impressed with the quality. The Crepe Nana (with Roquefort and pear) was very unusual and very tasty. The pate was on par with other good French restaurants in DC. I thoroughly enjoyed my pork medallions, while my husband's steak was also quite good, though maybe not a full 5 (more like a solid 4). And both of the desserts (the profiterole with ice cream and the chocolate mouse) were outstanding.

All this is to say - definitely worth the visit. I personally want to try their brunch next!

Delicious food and great service. The wait staff was great and helped us navigate the wheel-chair ramp, and went out of their way to provide desserts that we requested that weren't on the menu. My dad and stepmom have been having dates here for over a decade and have had a number of events here too ♥️ Can't go wrong with Le Chat Noir!

I only ordered a creme brulee and a French baguette for delivery, the truth is that it feels authentic, the bread is delicious, hot with butter is out of this world and the creme brule delicious, I will definitely return to eat at the place to try their dishes.
Had a great time eating at Le Chat! Food was yummy, and we tried the suzette en flambé which was cool! People watching was also entertaining. Overall great experience and hope to return again soon!

was the most disappointing experience. We paid almost $150 for food that wasn't even decent. The creme brulee was just bad. There was no "creme" about it. It was so thick you could cut it with a knife and it didn't taste good. It's my favorite food ever and I threw it away. And it was tiny for the price. We ordered a $30 steak and it was the smallest little piece of meat with basic soggy fries. My husband got a crepe and it was pathetic. A tiny, messy, mound with Nutella more smeared on the container than in the crepe. If the meal was a quarter of the price it may of been a neutral experience. But a tiny creme brulee that I threw away isn't worth $14.

Outstanding Indian restaurant often overlooked. Delicious and delicate flavors, well executed dishes with authentic spice and presentation. Owner oversees service and makes every effort to make your meal memorable. Favorites are all their Briyani rice dishes,  Elaichi Gosht  and  Murgh Tikka Masala.
Best Indian food in the immediate area. Really nice flavors in some of the dishes. Ask owner / manager for recommendations. Just opened back up for lunch with a special menu.

I was considering a 4 star review bc the waitress seemed really pushy at first, barely giving us enough time to see the menu but she ended up being very helpful and kind and incredibly attentive. The food was absolutely amazing, can't recommend the goat cheese Naan enough! Everything was piping hot and so, so delicious! I wish I lived in DC just so that I could eat here regularly.

Arguably the best lamb vindaloo in DC! Excellent service on a Thursday night. I have passed by this restaurant many times and finally decided to give this a try. It is indeed a hidden gem in the neighborhood. Consistent quality at a reasonable price. Half price bottles of wine on Thursday evenings.

The food was fantastic. Masala art is a quiet nice restaurant that offers great authentic Indian food. The service here was great as well. I was a big fan of all the nan options to go with your food. When I'm in the area I would for sure stop by here again.

Staff argued me too long to convince them to toast my wrapped chipotle sandwich until I felt I am asking for something wrong.
The place is good, clean and big.
The wrapped chipotle steak and cheese was good as the other subway restaurants. It is hard to find a free parking to get into the mall  where the subway located. But you don't need to dig too deep in the mall to find it, as it is located next to the garage entrance.
BTW I got that wrapped chipotle steak and cheese plus small chips and a drink and I payed almost $12 which is too much.
Another Veggie Delight helping me toward my weight loss goal. I love that these places are so reliably similar!
Went to get a sandwich and the way they make sandwich is worst. Would not go there
Its clean and inviting, I enjoy my visits there.
nice employees and good food

If someone has a bunch of store coupons..in this case from subway restaurant and wanted to share some with a customer out of just being nice especially when everything is so expensive these days..is that wrong? Well i did so a week ago and then the nasty subway owner who turns all rude and ugly tells me to not share the coupons with people in his store and that if i wanted to i need to do it outside his store. Is there some sort of policy to this? If there was he could have told me nicely instead he was just so rude. i wanted to say more but decided to just leave and not give him a cent of my money. I was just helping someone save some money thats all. Instead i was yelled at and treated badly. Please DON’T give your business to this mean and nasty old man. There are many other subway restaurants in this neighborhood..go there.

I was shopping and a nice lady who was waiting her turn to order, looked at me and extended her hand with some coupons asking me if I wanted them, I thanked her and asked the man who was there.  I asked him if I could use them and he answered angrily ask her, she was the one who gave them to you, she very kindly told me that I could only use them with the specific orders that the coupons said, the man, not happy and very disrespectful, told her not to return it to make sure that if he wanted to help someone he did it outside the store I told the man that he didn't need to talk to him like that the lady left saying that she would complain later she wanted to keep saying things and I told her to shut up that she had to learn to treat people people with respect i feel really bad for the girl if you're reading this i'm sorry you had to go through that just for trying to make a nice gesture.

Horrible customer service. Cashier refused to accept my promo offer from Subway.com because it didn't have QR code. He wouldn't even provide a reason for refusing to use it. I asked for manager.. tells me "manager isn't available". Seems like management left him by himself. Taste of my sandwich has been better at other subway locations.

Ordered online Italian sub. They sent me a veggie sun filled with green and cheese. I call the location employee asked me if I'm sure accuses me of lying. I told him I took a picture. He back pedal. Waiting on refund. How do you screw up order in a pandemic with no physical customers in store.  American workforce gets worst by the day!
Absolutely terrible. I got a turkey sandwich. The bread was old and flaky and dry. The meat was okay. I noticed that the tuna salad in the food bins was dark and dry and looked old as well.

I spotted this place as we drove by on a work detail and went back after we were done. I’m glad I did. I got the original steak & eggs. At $22 it was a little pricey but the food was of good quality. Everything had a fresh taste and appearance. The chocolate/banana milkshake was also a bit pricey at $8 but excellent as well. Good flavor and consistency. The restaurant had a bright, clean appearance and the staff was friendly & attentive. Due to the prices it’s not somewhere I’d frequent but I’d definitely go back if I was in the area.

The original greasy spoon has finally completed their renovations. Same food in a more comfortable space. Eggs and potatoes were the tastiest items. Didn't like the breakfast meats. Coffee could be better. The service was great.

This place is nice to chill and have a bite to eat. Took my son by there for breakfast and we loved it. The country fried steak with gravy and biscuits was delicious. The waffle was made with fresh blueberries and my son thought they were too sweet 😋 that says alot coming from a 11 yr old. Coffee was perfect to end such a hearty meal.  This place was a vibe I'll be back.

I loved it!! Wanted to try something new and asked what's popular. He recommended the Philly cheese steak. Hesitant since it's usually not my favorite but oh my god! It was great!! My favorite Philly cheese steak!! My boyfriend got the burger and it was really good for a diner style burger!! The fries, meat and bread was all great!! ❤️❤️ waiter was also very nice!!

The food was absolutely amazing! Yes, we spent like $40 per person but we got a lot of food to be fair. Besides, the price was WELL worth the portion sizes they give you. I've had salmon breakfast sandwiches many other places and I usually get 2 because they are so small, I did that here and that was a mistake. I was so full after just one. All of the food had a lot of flavor. It was only street parking, but typically you can find a spot close by. The people working their also seemed friendly. We will definitely be repeat customers; we'd choose Steak n' egg over IHOP any day.

This is the ABSOLUTE Best Chicken sandwich my wife and I have ever tried! The employees are extremely nice and friendly. The owner came out and greeted us to make sure we enjoyed our visit. I was overwhelmed by his hospitality. This is a MUST HAVE location here in Washington DC!

Excellent food and Service. The food was very hot when I took my first bite…so maybe wait a few minutes after you get your food to dig in! The older gentleman who helped us at the front was very kind and brought us ketchup to our table for our fries without even asking him. The amount of fries you get is unbelievable, more than enough for everyone to have some! Very tasty too! They have a sign out front saying “Covid free zone”..made me laugh, but they actually have some air cleaners hanging throughout the establishment to clean the air. Overall I was very pleased with my visit here.

Our burgers was juicy, hot and flavorful. They will load you up with plenty of nice warm flavor French fries in a cup inside a bag, the french fries flavor remind me, when I used to get boardwalk french fries back in the day. The milkshake was flavorful as well. Great staff and friendly atmosphere.

I pass Z Burger at least once a day, parking here is intimidating but I got the courage to illegal park and risk it. I ordered a double cheese burger fully loaded. The burger tasted great no complains the burger and toppings fit in this bun they use allot of fountain drinks were out of order and had a funny taste.

It’s always yummy and the shakes are incredible. But the best part is the owner is there a lot of the time and he’s maybe the sweetest guy ever. Always recognizes us even though we only come in maybe once a week or so. The people make this place the best

Literally one of THE WORST dining experiences I have had…. And I eat out a lot.  I’ll provide more detail below for those who are interested.
1) We were a group of 5.  4 of us showed up at 8p, and 1 more was going to join us at 8:30/45.  The first 4 of us sought to get drinks at the bar.  They encouraged us to grab our table and order with our waitress.  We took their lead and sat at our table.  Menus and water came, but then no one came back to take our drink orders.  They were just waiting for the 5th person to show up.  Understandable.  We went back to the bar after 10+ minutes to order drinks, they apologized profusely, and sent the waitress over right away.
2) We then ordered drinks, including one for the person who had not yet arrived.  15 more minutes passed, and no drinks came.  Turns out they couldn’t figure out the ingredients for one of the drinks, and instead of ask us OR bring the other four drinks, they just made us wait… until we complained again.
3) Finally the drinks came and they took our food order.  After a decent wait (and, mind you, it was not that busy that night), they brought 3 of our 5 dishes out.  Those with dishes started eating.  The remaining two dishes *never came.*  After 10+ minutes of waiting, we complained again, they rushed to check with the kitchen, and then apologized (for the Nth time) that the orders had not been input correctly.
4) We then ordered another round of drinks while waiting for the additional dishes to be made.  15+ minutes later, those drinks finally arrived.  We were steamed that they couldn’t get anything right.
5) When the burger finally arrived (one of the originally missing items), it looked great.  We had ordered it medium — intentionally not medium rare because we didn’t want it all that pink on the inside.  The center of the burger was RAW BEEF.  In their rush to address the missing items, they severely undercooked the meat.

No other way to describe this experience than (a) HORRIBLE for us as guests, and (b) EMBARRASSING for them as a restaurant.  When you are an establishment with $34 entrees on the menu, we expect better.  Needless to say, we will not be going back there again.

Walked up on this place four minutes before they opened. They requested that we wait outside for a while. Perhaps to finish pre-shift. Fine.

Everything was fairly tasty. The cornmeal fried oysters were a hit with my cousin and I. The wedge salad had a tart/citrus but savory taste to it. Topped with yummy thick cut bacon. Entrees were sort of bland. I enjoyed the cauliflower purée and sprouts. However, the scallops had a rough texture to them. I’m not exactly sure why they tasted rough/dry. Usually scallops have a soft, buttery taste to them. My cousin did enjoy the lemon caper sauce. I’d say the sauce was enjoyable. We also ordered the crab cakes, please order with caution. They aren’t lump crab, if you’re a local. No pic because the dish did not look appetizing.

Reason I’m rating this place a two is because I go to restaurants for more than ambiance. I go for food and service. The server was nice and knowledgeable. He neglected to inform me that he charged me twice after we requested a split check. My cousin paid and tipped in cash. After calling the manager tonight when I noticed, she said she couldn’t find the check. I told her I can email everything to her. I asked for email address and she told me it was on the website. Second inconvenience. I went to website and there’s no email address.

There’s nothing about this place that would make me return after the manager on duty’s communication with me. Do better.

Consistent, Cozy, Expensive. For a long standing neighborhood restaurant, this one leans towards the expensive side. It is a small space. So reservations are recommended. Try the bar area if there is only two in your party. Service across most restaurants has been impacted by COVID. Bucks is no exception. We had one waiter serving more than her share of tables. While the waiter was helpful and gracious, waiting too many tables impacted her ability to be attentive and engaging. The food is consistently good but pricey. Unlike other restaurants, Bucks has not modified it's menu selections due to the pandemic.

Glad to see that I am not the only one with a very bad experience...A nice and warm evening of November, I decide to eat out on a terrace. The restaurant looks adorable, beautiful deco. I look at the menu and decide I can definitely find something nice to eat in this decor. When I got informed that ALL the tables outside are reserved. There is NOBODY outside, it is not even 6 pm. I ask if they can accommodate me since I am alone and will finish my meal before the reservations arrive. They check their tablet, and confirm: it is impossible to sit people outside because people have reserved for in one hour ! I cannot believe. I decide to take my time to go around and find another restaurant and I walk for 20 minutes, looking at menus and atmospheres. When I pass again in front, the terrace is still EMPTY ! They are waiting for people to come in one hour. imagine if you are the real owner of the restaurant.... I will be so angry ! End of the story: I ended up in a lovely, absolutely delicious restaurant across the street, spent a bunch of $ on treating myself, including appetizer, entree, dish, wine, cocktail and dessert, and giving a very generous 30% tips (well deserved) Your loss. Hopefully the restaurant owner will read this review: time to change your team buddy !

I visited for the first time 2 days ago (Fri) for a birthday getogether at the bar. After waiting over 15 mins to be acknowledged (wearing bright red and waving, saying excuse me to the male bartender with the ponytail who ignored me the whole time) I asked one of the ladies sitting at the bar if she had been served. She said others had been complaining about him being rude and not providing service throughout the night. Thankfully, a second bartender, Evan, arrived and took my order and was attentive to bar customers for the rest of the time I was there. Overall I liked the restaurant and enjoyed the turkey burger and old fashioned, but initial service was absolutely unacceptable. There's too much competition in the DMV for any restaurant to provide poor customer service.

Good location. Parking is street so you win some, you lose some. Staff was nice. Patio dining area is minimal yet cool, although I didn't use it. My only gripe is that I ordered 4 pita wraps to go through the app for pickup. The app asks for the name that corresponds to each wrap that you order so that every person in your group knows which item is theirs. No reference was placed on the wraps. Unfortunately, we had to open each wrapper and pull open the pita to see which one was for which person. Other than that, it was all gravy.
good food, good service, and good management! The best part of this CAVA is its friendly and high-efficient staff. Their excellent performance is way over a fast-food chain restaurant.

A person in training served my food just right now (5:15 pm). She does not know the amounts to serve for topins. I am so disappointed. I only half meal and they charged me 17.79 !! Btw, did not have a customer service actitud. And her coo-worker same. I told them they were serving not the right quantity and they were careless. Also, food presentation on the plate..!so messy . Unbelievable

I came in with a last-minute order for 14 people after our previous lunch plans fell through. The folks at CAVA were not only super sweet but also lightning fast! I was in and out with lunch for my whole team in under 15 minutes. Fantastic service & staff, they saved my day!
My go-to place for good, tasty, healthy, moderately-priced food in the Tenleytown area.  Nearby on-street or metered parking always available. Or use public transit.

OMG ..... had not eaten at Panera for a long time because ordering in store (any store) is an ordeal, it always takes too long no matter what is ordered from a simple coffee or pastry to an actual meal.
today, due to rain we ordered on line ,we got chicken soups , well what a disappointment, the container is too small to actually be a bowl, ($10.00) literally looks like mud water and the taste was horrific.
and barely any chicken in it.
was so disappointed with the size that i walk over to Crispy Chicken (literally on the same block) and ordered their chicken soup ($5) night and day difference !!!  a little bigger container,  the flavor and appearance so much better, the manager of this Panera store should walk over to crispy chicken and get a chicken soup and compare it.
in the pictures, the brown soup is Panera

Service was friendly, and the lively atmosphere is nice, but the line to place an order was slow, and the food took forever to come out. I got a couple sides of mac and cheese and that was it, yet it took probably 15-20 minutes to come out.

I ordered to go, so it was only once I got back home that I came to discover that the mac and cheese that I waited for was not even the full serving. The larger side was roughly only 2-3 full, while the smaller cup was probably 3/4 full. It tasted great, but the hassle overall wasn't worth it.

Panera has lost its mind. They think there food is so special that they are charging $10 for a HALF sandwich? No thanks, I will take my money elsewhere. There was nothing special about Panera before so there is definitely no reason to go there now. Go spend your money at Coffee Nature a few blocks away. It is a wonderful family owned restaurant with great food and good prices.

Overall, I think that this is a great study spot with potential to be a regular stop for me and my pals. Service was snappy, a very nice lady cleaned off our table when we came in, and our orders of mac & cheese were HUGE. My only complaint is that 45 minutes into our dining experience, the manager came over and said that they were closing the store. It was 1:15 p.m. on a Sunday - we were not given any explanation for this sudden shut down. To say that this was bizarre is an understatement. We were given free pastries to make up for the inconvenience and were promptly shuffled out. 5 stars for the free goodies - 3 stars for the absolute pandemonium caused by people evacuating the building.

UPDATE: After my party switched locations for continued studying, we walked passed the Panera approximately 4 hours later and it was OPENED. A new staff had taken over and service was back to normal. SO STRANGE.

There is not a single time I had ever received an order that was orderly like it was supposed to be. Yet I always cleaned any mess in the restaurant be it in the bathrooms or dinning area, organizing the chairs in the restaurant always and I mean always. I would try to clean up even the outside of the restaurant whenever it would be so dirty. I ate here several times and wouldn't bother to complain anymore since I had tried at other locations and still didn't change. I kind of learned to go along with the flow such that if they served me a disorderly meal, I would just accept it without questions. I wouldn't be so happy though as if I had received an orderly meal which I would need. All in all, this Panera location, please stay away from it because I was doing good for them while they insisted on doing evil to me

I've worked as a delivery driver for almost 2 years. What I did not like about working for this company was, I was basically getting robbed. I was always getting underpaid. I was working part-time but my paycheck was always at least $200 short. The assistant manager, Brent is a great guy, it's just I did not appreciate how little I was getting paid.

Not good business practice. The app said my pizza was deliver but it was not. I called to check on delivery status but no one picked up my call tried calling to speak with manager no one picked up I will not order from here again
They made the exact food with the perfect aroma and taste.

So I like ordering my pizza from this location. It's very close to my job. My last encounter with them was today and the lady who I spole with on the phone was so nasty. I mean she kept cutting me off, not listening to anything I was saying. I believe customer service is important and if you want people to support to business you can't be rude. It's not my fault that you don't have enough workers on staff. If I'm paying for your food, then I expect to be treated with respect. Then I called again to find out the status of my pizza and I was put on hold for almost 20 minutes. Again...poor customer service. I don't get it. I'm very upset about this. I've missed my lunch time and I gotta warm up the pizza that I paid for to be warm. Unacceptable. food is good, service leaves MUCH to be desired.

Rude!!!! Worst place ever!!!!!  We ordered online n picked it up and the lady was so rude. I told her our order was ready for pickup and she said you gave you wait five min. And when I added soda she told me to wait another five minutes because she was busy. After five min asking again she was so rude and said next time I N won’t give out unless you pay online. I mean what the hell is that. Never going here again!!!!!

As an annual patron at Matisse since 2014 I have to say that the atmosphere and food have made no compromises in light of the pandemic. This is an excellent place to escape for a meal with family and friends. Staff and chefs are fantastic and deliver excellence.

We went here for our anniversary and even listed that on the reservation. The food was good, but the service was all over the place. The beginning of our meal felt rushed and we were done with appetizers and entrees after 45-50 min. We were then presented the dessert menu and ordered. We did not end up receiving our dessert for another 40 minutes. Never were we told that there would be such a delay. If that had been the case because of a kitchen backup, we would have understood and chose not to have ordered a dessert. Instead we were stuck at our table with no one even stopping by to refill our drinks. We were left feeling like we had been forgotten - definitely not what you would want on a special night out.

Portion sizes also varied widely. My husband's meal was incredibly small while mine was almost too large. He would have left our expensive dinner hungry if mine wasn't large enough to share.

That was, my husband and I, our 1st time at Matisse.
The décor was quite elegant.
The menu offered a nice variety of dishes.
We all like the meals that we ordered.
It would have bee  perfect if:
-the $15 blueberry mojito had a little bit more rum. I could feel that it was super light, since after two sips of any alcoholic beverage, I already feel tipsy, feeling I did not get with it.
- If we could have had more bread. Once piece was only served at the beginning of the meal.
- If the music could have been less loud.
Almost a perfect evening!

I'm baffled. The night I ate at Matisse, the chicken was not fully cooked, I tasted 1 bite; very bland, the vegetables greasy, they served fries, like I was eating at McDonalds.  I ordered a white wine, and I later found out they gave me a lower label than I paid for.  This is NOT French cooking. When I was in Nice, $7 got me the best coq au vin; this restaurant's food is like a fast-cook diner. K. Steinhart

Food was better than expected. Oysters were sublime, and the lamb was cooked to perfection. The sauce paired perfectly! Only word of caution is if its for a special occasion, I specified a birthday on the celebration - but there was nothing special out of the kitchen to that end

Yosaku has been my family's go-to restaurant for years. We love that there is something for everyone: the meat-eaters, the fish-lover, and the vegetarian. The vegetable sushi dinner, seaweed salads, bean sprouts, agedashi tofu, and teriyaki salmon are particularly delicious. 10/10 recommend! Come support Yosaku!

Great service, the waitress was very accomodating and very nice. The fastest we ever had Sushi deliver to the table. Food was awesome!!! The environment was intimate and quiet. They have Happy Hour Sushi everyday from 5-7:30, too bad we got there late, but it was worth it. Whenever we come back to Washington DC, we're definitely coming back. Highly recommend it.

This is the real deal if you're looking for really authentic Japanese food! There are some dishes here that you wont easily find at your average Japanese restaurant, like sukiyaki or unagi. Definitely worth it to come here!

Reasonable Japanese lunch at $9-12. On Mondays you'll get happy hour price all day, sushi (nigiri) $1 each. Sushi is a bit dry but ok. Shimesaba sushi (mackerel seasoned in vinegar) is my favorite. Nabeyaki udon was great! One of the pitfalls was the bathroom. It was clean but the whole area near bathroom was stinky. Another was that they had hot tea but served us cold water without asking.

I hadn't been for ages, due to COVID. I realize now that I should have gone back ages ago! The food is delicious and the service is excellent. I had the bento box lunch with mackerel and enjoyed every bite!

Pizza was hard as a brick and the wings were horrible. I ordered a meat lovers pizza and a pepperoni pizza. How do you have such a great reputation in the community and serving low grade food like this. This was a waste of $79.00. Maybe the animals outside will enjoy this garbage.

Went here for a late night dinner in a weekday. It was not busy. Food was delicious. We got a spicy chicken pizza. Spicy level was very low even it said it was spicy. They also serve beer abd other sodas. Order was processed within 15 mins. Employees were very frindly and saw they are cleaning tables after someone leave.

I went for dinner on Thursday night, and let me tell you Angelico pizzeria totally satisfied my Italian food craving!

We dined at the cafe and felt very safe. There was also outside patio seating.

To start we ordered the caprese salad. Very very fresh!

They make their sandwiches with HOMEMADE focaccia. It was absolutely so comforting, so fresh. We ordered the Turkey sandwich because it also came with homemade pesto sauce. I devoured it.

Next we ordered the spinach and artichoke pizza and Italian calzone.
The toppings were flavorful and the calzones were soooo cheesy and pipping hot.

For dessert we ordered a slice of the chocolate cake. It was super thick and dense. With a little cannoli cream on top, it was a great end to our meal.

I was very happy to support Angelico pizzeria. The owner is so nice and has multiple locations. SUPPORT LOCAL! You won’t regret it
As a New Yorker who's in DC for college, this establishment makes me feel like I'm at home. Great pizza.

A picture is worth 1000 words. The pizza is about as average as it looks. When you can't even make a pizza look appealing, the rest of the experience is bound to downhill.

There is no problem with any sauce/cheese ratio or any overt negatives about the taste. It is just not the pizza you should ever bother with when you're in DC and have other options.

I have been searching for the best New Haven style apizza for many years. I live in Annapolis and recently purchased a vehicle at a dealership in Bethesda. I had time to burn and when I searched for the best pizza near me I came across Pete’s.

I was eager to indulge in my favorite style pizza so I stopped in for lunch. Dare I say, I was not prepared for the pure awesomeness of Pete’s. It’s one of my top 5 pizza joints in Maryland. The food and service were extraordinary and I will be a repeat customer when I get my car serviced.

A quiet and low key spot for lunch. The pizza is good with that great crust. The chocolate Cannoli and Black Cherry fountain soda tops it off for me every time I visit. The staff is friendly, the restaurant is well maintained, and prices are reasonable.

Awful pizza. Bought the New Haven Clam pizza and it was bone dry & flavorless. The clams were small, rubbery and had no flavor. The pizza was also stiff as a rock when picked up (see photo). The dough was all crunch, like it had been fried and did not have the signature chewy texture of good pizza.

Called to complain about the order and the manager was very rude, said they would issue a credit to us and hung up the phone. Doubtful we'll see that credit or ever want to go back and use it.

What a terrible place.

Great service and pizza, quality ingredients, great dough, and great selection of fountain drinks.

Be mindful of ordering the small pizzas. They come loaded with toppings, which causes the center to get soggy, and that is my only beef herere with this pace.

Placed an online order for pickup. Didn’t see til I got back home that the bottoms of both my pizzas were completely charred. It made it very much inedible. I emailed customer service about this seeing if I could get a refund and never heard back.
